\newlabel{fig:category_scatter}{{6}{24}{Category-level \rmse vs.\ \mae scatter plot for eight modern architectures. Each point represents one model's mean error within a category. The near-perfect linear correlation ($R^2 > 0.99$) confirms that model rankings are consistent across the two error metrics, indicating that findings based on \rmse generalise to \mae . The full nine-model variant is provided in Appendix~\ref {sec:app_dual_plots}}{figure.caption.17}{}}
